   <talk_paragraph index="n709_trader_lucita-accepting-b" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="300511" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n709_trader_lucita-accepting-c" mid="38" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(You oberve the letter)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="37"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant Lucita$<BR>As you can see, it's a lump of l-letters. Pedro usually collects books that he requested from the adventurers and sells them to me, and this was between those books.<BR>
Others are ordinary novels, but this seemed a little special....</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n709_trader_lucita-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n709_trader_lucita-accepting-d" mid="40" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>They're letters from Karacule.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="39"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#7e12d2>(The old letters mostly look like they were sent to Karacule from various people.</FONT><BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>Usual greetings asking for Karacule's well-being follows.<BR>You read a letter about meeting up at the usual place since the sender was coming here after a long time)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
